trying to fit in. As an only child, it was hard for me to relate to anyone. I don't enjoy hanging out with my parents much or talking to them. My parents left Guatemala when they were around 20 years old and they had a really rough childhood. When they left, they were completely clueless to what life was like outside of Guatemala. They told me something very important about coming here and the other thing that they mentioned is, if I focus on school, I can make my parents proud. Mr. and Mrs. Williams have given me opportunities that I may not had, such as myself working towards becoming a veterinarian. After constructing this building, I will be applying for my GED at the Saddleback campus.
